          <p><a href="http://www.turismocoruna.com/web/corTurServer.php?idSecweb=97&idInfo=31&idCategoria=50"><b>Trip Advisor</b></a></p>
          <p>Some of the best restaurants can be found on Rua Olmos and Rua Estrella, which are found running parallel to the port near the Gardens of Mendez Nunez.  There are also many restaurants within the Plaza Maria Pita.</p>
          <p>Galicia is known for its excellent seafood and you will see this reflected in its menus.  Other traditional dishes include Tortilla Espanola, Pimientos de Padron, Patatas Bravas, Empanadas, and sliced ham and cheese.  A popular dessert, or breakfast, is churros con chocolate. La Postreria is an enjoyable modern dessert establishment.</p>
          <p>I do not recommend eating non-Spanish cuisine in La Coruña as it tends to be very disappointing (unless you like school cafeteria style pizza).</p>
